name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'NotoSansMono-SemiCondensedThin', Everything looks good.

Noto Sans Mono SemCond Thin Regular (NotoSansMono-SemiCondensedThin.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

(NID 16 + 'Space' + NID 17) 'Noto Sans Mono SemiCondensed Thin' ≠ 'Noto Sans Mono SemCond Thin' (NID 1).

(NID 16 + 'Space' + NID 17) 'Noto Sans Mono SemiCondensed Light' ≠ 'Noto Sans Mono SemCond Light' (NID 1).

name

MS NID 6

NID 6 is 'NotoSansMono-SemiCondensed', Everything looks good.

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '

NID 6 is 'NotoSansMono-SemiCondensedExtraBold', Everything looks good.

Noto Sans Mono SemCond ExtBd Regular (NotoSansMono-SemiCondensedExtraBold.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

(NID 16 + 'Space' + NID 17) 'Noto Sans Mono SemiCondensed ExtraBold' ≠ 'Noto Sans Mono SemCond ExtBd' (NID 1).

underlinePosition should be a negative and underlineThickness not 0 or negative.

underlinePosition is '-100'.
underlineThicknes is '50'.
